main event: A rancher and his family saw 3 bright, flashing objects traveling at high speeds from north to south in Soledad, California on February 27, 1955.
interesting points: The objects were at different altitudes and flashed brightly, disappearing behind hilltops and reappearing.
The objects made sharp turns and changed direction suddenly.
The rancher stated he had seen many jet planes and aircraft before, but these objects were unlike anything he had ever seen.
The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes.

In a separate incident on March 2, 1955, one round object the size of a nickel held at arm's length was observed for a few seconds in Soledad, California. Pilots scrambled to search the area but could not confirm the sighting.
sighted object: Three bright, flashing objects; one round object
witnesses: Rancher and his family; unspecified witness
